title: Global stocks slip, U.S. yields rise on retail sales data
text: A gauge of global equities edged lower on Tuesday and U.S. Treasury yields climbed as a stronger-than-anticipated report on retail sales raised the possibility that a second rate cut by the Federal Reserve this year could be pushed back by several months.

title: Dow Jones Leads Sluggish Stock Market; Banks Not Much Help

title: US Stocks Little Moved as Earnings Roll In Tuesday
text: U.S. stocks indexes moved little on Tuesday, with major companies starting to report earnings.

title: China startup deals shrink as fundraising for investors plummets
text: Chinese startups continue to weather tough times as private investors, caught in a cash crunch, are concentrating money into fewer deals. China’s deal-making activity for startups in the six months ended June halved from a year ago to 1910, according to data from consulting firm ChinaVenture’s research arm.

title: Better-Than Expected Retail Sales in June

title: Oil gains as Iran tensions outweigh U.S. supply boom
text: Oil prices rose on Tuesday as tensions in the Middle East outweighed the impact of a resumption of production in the Gulf of Mexico after Hurricane Barry and a boom in U.S. supply from shale oil.

title: Oil firms as U.S. supply concerns ease but Iran tension lingers
text: Oil prices rose on Tuesday as a resumption of output in the Gulf of Mexico after Hurricane Barry and a boom in U.S. supply due to shale oil countered tensions in the Middle East.

title: Oil Holds Losses As U.S. Output Returns After Gulf Storm Weakens
text: Oil held losses below $60 a barrel after decline in two weeks as a tropical storm that shut three-quarters of U.S. Gulf of Mexico production moved  inland.

title: Wall Street finds blockchain hard to tame after early euphoria

title: Stocks Mixed As Big Banks Report; Treasuries Slip: Markets Wrap

title: China says misleading to suggest it needs trade deal due to slowing economy
text: China's Foreign Ministry said on Tuesday that it was misleading to suggest Beijing needed a trade deal with the United States because its economy was slowing, following a tweet by U.S. President Donald Trump.

title: The "Insurance" Cut Worry
